{St Nicholas' Church.} This church is the oldest and biggest church in our area. The earliest record of it is 1122,but it is thought that it is a bit older than that. It originally had 5 bells but now it has 6. The church is still being added to- a Vestry is the latest addition. {Vicar-Rev. Rimmer.}
{The United Reformed Church.} This was built in 1939, but its congregation began their meetings 100 years ago. It has many clubs and groups attached to it. {Vicar-Rev. Ewart.}
{St Michael and All Angels.} Built only 30 years ago, this is a modern church. It has one small bell in a small tower. {Vicar-Rev. Miles.}
